Czech Stocks: Komercni Banka, New World Resources Shares Move

-- B y   K r y s t o f   C h a m o n i k o l a s
-- 
2011-08-25T15:43:46Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-25/czech-stocks-komercni-banka-new-world-resources-shares-move.html
The Czech Republic’s PX stock index
rose for a second day, gaining 1 percent to 1,025 at the 4:28
p.m. close in  Prague , its highest since Aug. 8.  The following were among the most active equities on the
Prague Stock Exchange today. Stock symbols follow company names.  Komercni Banka AS (KOMB)   climbed 2.9 percent to 3,500
koruna. The Czech unit of Societe Generale SA has advanced 14
percent in the past four days, heading for its biggest weekly
gain in more than two years. The stock was lifted to “buy”
from “neutral” at Goldman Sachs Group Inc. today.  New World Resources Plc (NWR CP) climbed 0.7 percent to 162
koruna, its second day of increases. The largest Czech coking-
coal producer was upgraded to “outperform” from “neutral” at
Credit Suisse Group AG.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Krystof Chamonikolas in Prague at 
 kchamonikola@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Stephen Kirkland at   skirkland@bloomberg.net  